11/ PayPal $PYPL
- Partnership with Alibaba (BABA) - PayPal has launched a global partnership with Alibaba, enabling consumers outside of China to shop across Alibaba sites in China. PayPal is now available as a payment method on Alibaba's wholesale marketplace, along with AliPay

10/ PayPal $PYPL
- Buy Now Pay Later (BNPL), also known as Pay-in-4 at PayPal is a service which lets customers pay for any item priced between $30 and $600 in four installments within six weeks, interest free and no impact on their credit score.

9/ PayPal $PYPL
- Similar to Cash App offering on share trading & crypto purchases, PayPal recently started to offer. Venmo generates only $12 per user while Square's Cash App generates $54 per user, so there's huge potential of optionality in the business.

8/ PayPal $PYPL
- Inspired by WeChat Pay (TCEHY) and AliPay (BABA), PayPal has ambition to grow Venmo as a Super App (features like, digital wallet, host of consumer services under one roof - direct deposit, check cashing, budgeting tools, bill pay, crypto support, BNPL, etc.)

7/ PayPal $PYPL
Reinvestment rate (w/ optionality) -
- PayPal is reinvesting Net Income back to the business at a high rate (more than 130%). Similarly, free cash flow is deployed back to the business at 90% annually over last 3-5 years.

6/ PayPal $PYPL
ROIIC & FCF-ROIIC -
- Company is generating ROIIC of 20% (incremental return over incremental capital invested) and Reinvesting at 130% annually to generate Compounding rate of 26-27% annually.

5/ PayPal $PYPL
Sales/Profit growth-
- Sales grew at 18% CAGR and Profit at 33% CAGR over last 3-years. View over last 5-years is not much different, 18% CAGR for Sales growth and 28% CAGR for Profit growth.
- Active accounts grew from 237M in 1Q18 to 392M in 1Q21, CAGR of 18.3%. https://t.co/OqoiZgTztO

4/ PayPal $PYPL
- Network effect: two-sided network benefit is valuable insight into the data of its consumers (demand side) and merchants (supply side), optionality to cross-sell range of products & services that are tailored to merchant's and consumer's needs. https://t.co/qbCOp86nmF

3/ PayPal $PYPL
- Pricing Power - PayPal has recently raised its processing fees for U.S. merchants from Aug. 2, the rate for each online PayPal or Venmo transaction will rise to 3.49% plus $0.49 -- compared to its previous rate of 2.9% plus $0.30 for most online transactions. https://t.co/npiAmDZtUg

2/ PayPal $PYPL
- Strong brand - in digital online payment for websites, PayPal has 54.3% market share, way ahead of second-placed Stripe. also, PayPal has developed strong household brands including Xoom, Hyperwallet, iZettle, Braintree, Venmo and Honey. https://t.co/msJjTkIktB
